Package Model

Class Inventory

  • java.lang.Object
    • Model.Inventory
  • public class Inventory
extends java.lang.Object
    The Inventory contains all the Part and Product objects that are currently in the inventory. Within the class exists one ObservableList per type of object.
    Author:
    JamesBundtrock

      • lookupPart

        public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Part> lookupPart​(java.lang.String partName)
        Returns an ObservableList of Part objects when given a partName to search for. This overloads the lookupPart method, as it uses a String type parameter, rather than int. Purposefully, it does not only populate the ObservableList with exact, full matches; it also populates it with partial matches and purposefully attempts to ignore case (upper vs. lower).
        Parameters:
        partName - The partName of the Part to be searched for within the entire inventory.
        Returns:
        An ObservableList full of all full and partial matches, irrespective of case

      • lookupProduct

        public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Product> lookupProduct​(java.lang.String productName)
        Returns an ObservableList of Product objects when given a productName to search for. This overloads the lookupProduct method, as it uses a String type parameter, rather than int. Purposefully, it does not only populate the ObservableList with exact, full matches; it also populates it with partial matches and purposefully attempts to ignore case (upper vs. lower). *
        Parameters:
        productName - The productName of the Product to be searched for within the entire inventory.
        Returns:
        An ObservableList full of all full and partial matches, irrespective of case

      • updatePart

        public static void updatePart​(Part selectedPart)
        Replaces a Part within the inventory with the Part given as a parameter. This is only successful if the partId of the Part passed to this method matches a partId within the inventory of Part objects. Since all partId fields must be unique for each and every Part object, this method replaces the first match, and only the first as there can be no second.
        Parameters:
        selectedPart - A new Part object to replace the matching Part within the inventory

      • updateProduct

        public static void updateProduct​(Product selectedProduct)
        Replaces a Product within the inventory with the Product given as a parameter. This is only successful if the productId of the Product passed to this method matches a productId within the inventory of Product objects. Since all productId fields must be unique for each and every Product object, this method replaces the first match, and only the first as there can be no second.
        Parameters:
        selectedProduct - A new Product object to replace the matching Product within the inventory

      • deletePart

        public static boolean deletePart​(Part selectedPart)
        Removes this Part from the inventory of Part objects. This is only successful if the partId of the Part passed to this method matches a partId within the inventory of Part objects. Since all partId fields must be unique for each and every Part object, this method replaces the first match, and only the first as there can be no second. If no Part object is found with a matching partId, the method returns false.
        Parameters:
        selectedPart - The Part object to be removed from the inventory
        Returns:
        A check on whether or not a Part object was removed

      • deleteProduct

        public static boolean deleteProduct​(Product selectedProduct)
        Removes this Product from the inventory of Product objects. This is only successful if the productId of the Product passed to this method matches a productId within the inventory of Product objects. Since all productId fields must be unique for each and every Product object, this method removes the first match, and only the first as there can be no second. If no Product object is found with a matching productId, the method returns false.
        Parameters:
        selectedProduct - The Product object to be removed from the inventory
        Returns:
        A check on whether or not a Product object was removed
